entry.value: Notes: Hydro is normalised and excluding pumping. Wind is normalised. Solar includes solar photovoltaics and solar thermal generation. All other renewables includes electricity generation from gaseous and liquid biofuels, renewable municipal waste, geothermal, and tide, wave & ocean.
Ren. electricity in all other transport modes
* In period 2004-2010 all consumed biofuels are included in this category; as of 2011 only those compliant with Articles 17 and 18 of Directive 2009/28/EC.
Fuel used in transport (as defined in Article 3)
Note: All calculation provisions set out in Directive 2009/28/EC are applied to the total numerator and the total denominator
All fuel consumed for heating and cooling
Note: total includes all elements of "gross final consumption of energy" other than electricity and for other pruposes than transport
Article 5: Gross final consumption of energy from renewable sources
Note: electricity used in transport is included in transport and thus not included in electricity
Article 2 (f): Gross final consumption of energy
